https://javadoc.io/doc/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-api/latest/io/jsonwebtoken/Jwts.html

This is a convenience method. It will first ensure a Claims instance exists as the JWT body and then set the Claims subject field with the specified value. This allows you to write code like this:

 String jwt = Jwts.builder().setSubject("Me").compact();

instead of this:

 Claims claims = Jwts.claims().setSubject("Me");
 String jwt = Jwts.builder().setClaims(claims).compact();